observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Management: 
Require the Municipal Treasurer and Other Accountable Officers to immediately complete the liquidation of the cash advances and ensure strict compliance of Sections 5 and 8 of COA Circular No. 97-002;

Designate other bonded employees with no outstanding cash advance as Special Disbursing Officer (SDO) for specific undertakings to prevent simultaneous or overlapping of cash advance to one particular SDO;

Require the Municipal Treasurer with Other Accountable Officers to reconcile with the Municipal Accountant their respective books of accounts at least quarterly; and 

Require the Municipal Accountant withhold the salaries of concerned personnel who failed to comply with the instructions on liquidation of their cash advances as provided under COA Circular No. 97-002.

We recommended the following: 
The Management review the lease contracts on rates of rental and make necessary action/amendment to align with the Municipal Tax Ordinance;

The Management execute a contract of lease for all stalls to secure the enforcement of the lease payments;

Exert more effort in collecting delinquent rental fees and issue notices of demand for rental payments inclusive of penalties from all delinquent market stallholders as soon as the payment falls due in accordance with its power to create sources of revenues; and

Henceforth, the Municipal Treasurer strictly implement the pertinent provisions of Municipal Tax Ordinance No. 03 Series 2013 and Republic Act No. 7160.

We recommended the following:

The Municipal Solid Waste Management Board through the Solid Waste Management Focal Person follow up the status of the approval of the plan;


Material Recovery Facility should be provided or established by the Municipality in the Hamtic New Public Market to promote segregation of waste through recycling and composting; and

We recommended the following:

The Municipal Mayor, as head of the GAD Focal Point System (GFPS), ensure the full implementation of the GAD programs, projects and activities of the Municipality as enumerated in the approved GAD Plan and Budget;

The GFPS review the GAD Plan and Budget and GAD Accomplishment Report, then, correct any inconsistency or inaccuracy found in these documents.

We recommended and Management agreed that:
The Municipal Mayor, as head of the GAD Focal Point System (GFPS), ensure the full implementation of the GAD programs, projects and activities of the Municipality as enumerated in the approved GAD Plan and Budget;
The GFPS review the GAD Plan and Budget and GAD Accomplishment Report, then, correct any inconsistency or inaccuracy found in these documents.

We recommended that: 

The agency create an inventory committee to conduct the physical count of all property and equipment owned by the LGU;

Prepare promptly the RPCPPE to be used as basis of the Municipal Accountant in booking up unrecorded PPE; and

We recommended that:

The Municipal Accountant exert effort to compel the concerned NGOs/POs to prepare and submit Fund Utilization Report;

Send demand letters regularly for the immediate submission of liquidation reports by the concerned NGOs/POs.

